snippet.textDisplay:
hey, i just got the corsair dark core rgb pro two days ago. mini review!

1. the wire that comes with it is stiff, it's not really great wired with the included cable, although the cable itself is high quality. i've mainly used it wireless and it paired instantly with no hassle.

2. the icue software was a bit intimidating, but after poking around you can make it pretty simple or super advanced.

3. idk if this is normal, but idk where to put my pinky...feels like even with the included side grip with the rest there's not much space for my ring finger and pinky. although after breaking it in for 2 days i haven't really noticed, likely not an issue at all after more usage. i don't think most people besides me would care anyways, my old mouse was just really good about that.

overall, i really like it. it's cheaper than a lot of other wireless mice with similar build quality and features but doesn't seem to lose out on performance or comfort (besides the pinky thing which i'll get used to) and in true corsair fashion it has lots of pretty lights. also i got the cheaper version with no qi charging, i think it's a waste to get that honestly, just plugging it in to change settings charges it a good amount.
